 rules that guarantee the best possible result for everyone. In religion, it is of course the hand of God that guides the world. In both cases, individuals are in a way playing against a superior being that always seems to win. In this volume, some of the cognitive mechanisms and cultural selective forces behind this are examined by specialists in different fields of science. The first contributions analyze theoretical and methodological issues; in later chapters, developments in the European history are explored from the perspectives of sociology and economic theory.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCooperationxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aCooperationxReligious aspects. 0aEconomicsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEconomicsxReligious aspects. 4aEvolution der Kooperation. 4aReligion. 4aTheologie. 4aTheorie der rationalen Entscheidung. 4aÖkonomie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh  aEconomics.  aEvolution of Cooperation.  aRational Choice Theory.  aReligion.  aTheology.1 aBulbulia, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodchild, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrüne-Yanoff, Till, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGwin, Carl R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamppinen, Matti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelson, Robert H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorth, Charles M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPyysiäinen, Ilkka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPyysiäinen, Ilkka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchjoedt, Uffe, econ